Detailed Description

Community of distribued Pools

The community is a dynamic group of process. The Community object is responsible to implement the distributed workstealing using active message of the network. The object is responsible to implement default method for Callback and Upcall method in order to defined the behaviors in case of errors. The Community is an Object (from Net::Group and Core::WorkSet inheritences) with an identifier generated by the Net::Group object.

Initialize a Community using a property field Default recognized options on command line are --community [-name <string>] [-join <global node="" identifier>="">]

Exceptions:
RuntimeError if bad name or incorrect join's globalid
RestartException if restart mode is selected
ServerException if start the process only as a checkpoint server
